main event: An illuminated object was sighted in Washington, D.C. on September 7, 1955.
interesting points: The object appeared round and glowing, with no sound emitted,The sighting lasted for approximately 1 minute,There were three witnesses to the sighting,The weather conditions were described as very good with almost no wind,The object disappeared over the Dalecarlia Reservoir.
location: Washington, D.C., District of Columbia, USA
witness description: Three men, including a photographer and a color photographer, observed the object.
